Not all neurotoxins are created equal — and not all are safe.

With all the viral complications making the rounds on social media — from muscle weakness to full-body paralysis and toxicity — it’s more important than ever to make sure your injector is using Health Canada–approved neurotoxins.

🇨🇦 Health Canada regulates the dose, quality, and safety of each product to help prevent serious complications. That’s why in Canada, we only trust these 5 approved brands, shown in the video:
Botox®, Nuceiva™, Dysport®, Xeomin®, and Letybo®.

⚠️ Always ask what product is being used, and be cautious of off-label or unapproved toxins. Your safety comes first.

✔️ It’s also essential that your injector knows when and how to alternate neurotoxins to prevent tolerance from building up over time — something only a trained professional will understand.

⚠️ Do NOT get Russian lips or M-shaped lips — here’s why. 👄

These popular styles may look striking on social media, but what you don’t see is what happens after the photos are taken — and I’m seeing a growing number of clients coming to me asking for dissolving due to complications. Here’s why:

1️⃣ Lumps, bumps & migration
These techniques often create unnatural pressure in the middle of the lips (the mucosal area), which leads to product migration — caused by both how the product is injected and what is used.

2️⃣ Premature aging
They can cause extra vertical lines around the upper and lower lips — lines that naturally appear with age, but are now forming earlier due to incorrect technique. These lines are extremely hard to treat due to their location and how the tissue behaves over time.

3️⃣ Difficult to fix — even after dissolving
Russian or M-shaped lips often leave behind structural changes. Even after dissolving, the lips may be prone to re-migration, making long-term correction very challenging.

Please understand: not every lip trend is meant for every lip shape. Just because something looks good in a photo doesn’t mean it’s sustainable — or safe — for you. The lips are one of the most dynamic, expressive areas of the face. Any injection here must be highly individualized and expertly done to protect your long-term beauty and facial harmony.

Avoid outdated techniques and untrained hands — your lips deserve expert care.

Remember: just because something looks good online doesn’t mean it’s right for your face. The lips are dynamic, expressive, and delicate — they need personalized, thoughtful treatment to keep them healthy and naturally beautiful over time.

Let’s prioritize healthy, balanced, age-supportive results — not trends.
